subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
Fig. 23
) 
0.9 mm
long. Basal piece very short, about 0.2-times of aedeagus length. Median lobe distinctly longer than parameres, robust in basal 0.8, then distinctly narrowed, lateral margin strongly sclerotized in distal 0.2 (
Fig. 23a
); membranous inner sac strongly sclerotized, with two long spines on each side (
Fig. 23b
); apophyses of median lobe extending to base of basal piece. Parameres broad in basal 0.6, then gradually narrowed towards the apices (
Fig. 23c
).
